ly hot and cold weather temperatures and other surprises that can make these days.</td></tr><tr><td scope="col" valign="top"><object data="/uploads/features/kelias.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/kelias.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/kelias.swf" /></object></td><td valign="top">LigoWave <strong>PTP equipment</strong> allows to establish connectivity even between very distant locations. This makes LigoPTP equipment suitable for rural connectivity where terrain is rough and power supply is very limited. &nbsp;Enormous potential available in rural areas should not be wasted and rapid return on investment using LigoWave solutions can be easily used by Internet service providers for quick expansion and use of the potential that is available in these areas.</td></tr><tr><td><object data="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" /></object></td><td>High spectral efficiency is typical for LigoPTP equipment.&nbsp; Combining digital signal processing, dual polarization <strong>antennas</strong> and proprietary W-Jet protocol these <strong>bridges</strong> have a high spectral efficiency of&nbsp;2.7 bit/Hz.</td></tr><tr><td><object data="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" /></object></td><td>OLED screen is installed in all the LigoPTP series radios. Using external OLED screen users can easily align the link, perform a link test with different packet sizes just after the deployment, find out various statistics about the link (<strong>wireless</strong>, ethernet, device status etc.), reset to defaults or reboot the device and even lock the equipment to avoid unvelcom