(63, 'LigoPTP 24', '<h2>PTP (new) products</h2><p>The LigoPTP 24-series product family is the next generation LigoWave product line targeting the growing demand for carrier-grade data transmission over microwave radio.  Operating in the 24 GHz unlicensed spectrum, this product delivers seamless connectivity at true full-duplex TCP payload of 108 Mbps.  The LigoPTP 24-series is a perfect building block for any modern future-proof wireless network, including mobile service providers, fixed data service operators, enterprise customers, and municipal and governmental networks, among others.  Apart from the full system capacity of 216 Mbps, the LigoPTP 24-series is loaded with feature-rich configuration options, including adjustable channel sizing (3.5 MHz, 7 MHz, 14 MHz, 28 MHz for ETSI or 5 MHz, 10 MHz, 20 MHz, 30 MHz for ANSI) and adjustable modulation schemes to match any application. The LigoPTP 24 product is also capable of providing up to 4 E1/T1 interfaces for legacy connectivity or other use.</p><p>The LigoPTP 24-series products showcase an array of advanced software mechanisms that provide optimal point-to-point connectivity for high throughput-demand links.  In this product line, LigoWave features proprietary PTP mechanisms, incorporating techniques such as hitless Adaptive Code and Modulation (ACM) technology, allowing operators to achieve high-capacity data transmission and improve link utilization.  This reduces both operational and capital expenditures for maintaining high-capacity links and also maintains the highest possible spectral link efficiency and data availability, even at the most challenging of link conditions.</p><br />Product contains:<ul><li>Full system capacity of 216 Mbps</li><li>Hitless Adaptive Coding and Modulation (ACM) technology</li><li>Antennas included:<ul><li>PTP 24-1: includes 1 ft. diameter, 35 dBi gain, slip-fit waveguide antenna</li><li>PTP 24-2: includes 2 ft. diameter, 40 dBi gain, slip-fit waveguide antenna</li></ul></li><li>Full outdoor unit architecture - no IDU needed</li><li>Adjustable channel sizing (3.5/7/14/28 MHz for ETSI or 5/10/20/30 for ANSI) and modulation schemes (QPSK, 16APSK, 32APSK, 64QAM, 128QAM)</li><li>Up to 4 T1 interfaces</li></ul>', '<h2>FODU general benefits</h2><ul><li>On average a FODU terminal consumes 20% less energy than IDU + ODU terminals with simillar configuration;</li><li>No need for special equipment room or rack means less cost for building the site and operational expenses;</li><li>Easy and convenient use for rooftop/ tower repeaters to extend the reach of radio, overcome line of sight issues that are typical for rugged terrain;As there is only one unit and no indoor unit it is much cheaper to keep the spare part stock, troubleshoot or replace the unit.</li></ul><h2>LigoPTP 24 benefits</h2><ul><li>Excellent system gain allows efficiently upgrade PDH radios to 108Mbps capacity avoiding the antenna size change;</li><li>Low power consumption enables Power over Ethernet operation and use of solar/wind power;</li><li>ACM (Adaptive Coding and Modulation) and ATPC (Automatic Transmit Power Control) for high availability and high density deployments;</li><li>Very high flexibility allow to configure the system to various channel bandwith, modulation scheme and capacity;</li><li>SNMP support for remote netwok monitoring and management;</li><li>LigoPTP 24 full outdoor unit is an excellent choice to backhaul the traffic from all outdoor base stations including GSM, CDMA, LTE or any other setup demandig up to 4 E1/T1 and Ethernet interfaces;</li><li>Use LigoPTP 24 to future-proof the backhaul network by preserving E1/ T1 connectivity and adding Ethernet for future use before migration to packet/ IP backhaul traffic;</li><li>LigoPTP 24 is ideal choice to backhaul traffic from all outdoor base stations including WiMAX, WiFi or any other point-to-multi-point wireless broadband technology;</li><li>In case Ethernet is the only interface needed, it is less costly and more convenient to use the UTP cable from the full outdoor unit directly to the Ethernet switch istead of coaxial cable from the outdoor unit to the indoor unit and another cable from CPE to the indoor unit data interface;</li><li>Low power consumption – up to 25W per terminal allows the use of alternative power sources like solar and wind.</li></ul>', 0, '2012-06-13 21:23:50', '2012-06-15 11:32:39'),
