(82, 'Overview', '<p>LigoWave delivers high reliability and great performance point to point (PTP) wireless solutions ideally suited for both small WISP and big carriers, small companies and large enterprises, municipal, public projects and others. LigoWave devices work in unlicensed and licensed frequency bands. LigoWave equipment combines the newest wireless technologies (including microwaves) and proprietary techniques to achieve the greatest results and provide great benefits for customers at an attractive price.LigoPTP product series is dedicated but not limited to the following solutions:</p> <ul><li>IP/Cellular backhaul</li><li>Broadband access connectivity</li><li>Rural connectivity</li><li>Private networks</li><li>Security and surveillance</li></ul> ', '', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(83, 'IP/Cellular backhaul', '<h2>WiMAX backhaul</h2><p>The LigoPTP 3-18 and LigoPTP 3-N devices operate in the licensed 3.4 – 3.7 GHz frequency band and can provide <strong>backhaul</strong> connectivity for WiMAX base stations allowing real data throughput up to 70 Mbps. With LigoPTP, <strong>WiMAX</strong> networks can grow flexibly and quickly.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/backhaul1.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>HotSpot backhaul</h2><p>LigoPTP 5-23, LigoPTP 5-N, LigoPTP 2-19, and LigoPTP 2-N are ideally suited for remote hotspot zones where there isn’t easily accessible wired connectivity. This allows for a hotspot installation to be completed very quickly with low cost. Hotspot zones can have <strong>backhaul</strong> throughput up to 70 Mbps.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/backhaul2.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>Mesh backhaul</h2><p>Similar to <strong>Hotspot backhaul</strong>, the LigoPTP 5-23, LigoPTP 5-N, LigoPTP 2-19, and LigoPTP 2-N radios working in the unlicensed 2.4 and 5 GHz bands reliably serve mesh networks with efficient <strong>backhaul connectivity</strong>. Thus mesh networks can be easily expanded over large areas without expensive wired lines.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/backhaul3.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>DSLAM backhaul</h2><p>ADSL technology is widely used by telcos for access connectivity for residential and enterprise customers. As DSLAM concentrates anywhere from 8 to 64+ users it needs high speed backhaul connectivity. <strong><u>Wireless backhaul</u></strong> to DSLAM is very attractive when no fiber exists and copper <strong><u>backhaul technologies</u></strong> don’t provide enough throughput. In this case LigoPTP 5-23 MiMo or LigoPTP 5-N MiMo provides DSLAM <strong>backhaul</strong> connectivity with an aggregate 180 Mbps of real data throughput.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/backhaul4.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>3G/IP backhaul</h2><p>Mobile operators utilize their physical tower infrastructure not only for voice services but also for mobile internet services. 3G technology requires reliable backhaul connectivity between towers. For this case the best choice is a wireless link which can be easily created with microwave PTP from LigoWave: LigoPTP 24.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/backhaul5.jpg" alt="" /></div>', '', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(84, 'Broadband access connectivity', '<h2>Last-mile dedicated access</h2><p>LigoPTP links can be effectively used both for <strong>backhaul</strong> and for access connectivity. This example illustrates last-mile connectivity with unlicensed band microwave LigoPTP 24 devices from an ISP to a shopping or business center. Such connectivity can be quickly done and exploitable without additional frequency fees. Achievable throughput is up to 100 Mbps full-duplex.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/broadband1.jpg" alt="" /></div><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><h2>Backup/redundant data links</h2><p>For some companies internet connectivity is critical for business operations. Such companies often require additional/backup data links to the internet. For backup links <strong>wireless</strong> connectivity is very practical choice. LigoPTP 5-N, LigoPTP 5-23 or LigoPTP 5-N MiMo, LigoPTP 5-23 MiMo are recommended for this application.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/broadband2.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>Fixed networks extension</h2><p>There are some places where wired lines can’t reach. In this case an ISP can effectively connect these hard to reach spots with <strong>wireless</strong> utilizing, for example, LigoPTP 2-N or LigoPTP 2-19. Aggregate throughput is up to 70 Mbps.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/broadband3.jpg" alt="" /></div>', '', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(85, 'Private networks', '<h2>Enterprise wireless networks</h2><p>Some enterprises (especially IT) want to have their own independent <strong>network</strong> infrastructure for secure communication without additional monthly costs. With <strong>wireless PTP</strong> technologies this need can be easily realized. For private connectivity we suggest unlicensed band devices like LigoPTP 5-23 MiMo, LigoPTP 5-23 or LigoPTP 2-19. </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/private1.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>Building-to-building connectivity</h2><p>Building-to-building <strong>wireless</strong> connectivity can be effectively used in areas under the same administrative policy like campus, hospital buildings, school and etc. Recommended LigoPTP devices are from the unlicensed band series: LigoPTP 5-23 MiMo, LigoPTP 5-23, LigoPTP 2-19.  </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/private2.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>LAN extensions</h2><p>In metropolitan areas, small internet service providers often connect <strong>LAN networks</strong> from near buildings together to bigger MAN network. If the building can’t be connected with cable, usually it can be connected with <strong>wireless</strong>. LigoWave recommends LigoPTP 5-23 MiMo or LigoPTP 5-N MiMo.  </p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/private3.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>Leased line (E1/T1) replacement</h2><p>Because E1/T1 leased lines are expensive, there is a demand for alternate, more cost effective solutions. One of them can be <strong>wireless PTP</strong> usage. LigoPTP effectively relays large volumes of small packets making it ideal for carrying E1/T1 traffic. In this scenario additional converters (can be provided from LigoWave) from E1/T1 to Ethernet are required.  </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/private4.jpg" alt="" /></div><br />', '', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(86, 'Rural connectivity', '<h2>Connectivity for rural areas</h2><p><strong>Rural</strong> areas often have a limited fixed network infrastructure, and it does not make financial sense for ISPs to run cable or wired connections to each customer. Therefore the only well-suited option is <strong>wireless connectivity</strong>. For high throughput (up to 180 Mbps) we recommend LigoPTP 5-N MiMo or LigoPTP 5-23 MiMo devices, but for less throughput (up to 70 Mbps) we recommend LigoPTP 5-N or LigoPTP 5-23 devices.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/rural1.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>Emerging markets</h2><p>Growing demands for technology in middle level countries (India, Cambodia, Costa Rica, Colombia, Puerto Rico and others) requires quick solutions from the telecommunication sector. <strong>Wireless solutions</strong> are very attractive in these cases. For emerging markets LigoWave can provide various <strong>PTP (Point-to-Point) solutions</strong> working both in licensed and unlicensed bands.</p>', '', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(87, 'Security and surveillance', '<h2>Government/Municipal networks</h2><p>The LigoPTP 4 and LigoPTP 5 series models are recommended for deployment in governmental or municipal networks. LigoPTP equipment ensures strong data encryption and proprietary data protocols, so there is no risk for the hijacking of sensitive data.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/video1.jpg" alt="" /></div><div style="text-align: center;"><br /></div><br /><h2>Public safety/IP video surveillance</h2><p>With <strong>wireless</strong> connectivity IP video cameras can be mounted in various places including traffic-lights, poles, walls, etc. LigoPTP 5, LigoPTP 2, or even LigoPTP 4 series <strong>products</strong> can be used in this case.</p><p><br /></p><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="/uploads/12-06-04/video2.jpg" alt="" /></div>', '', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(88, 'LigoPTP 2-N', '<p>LigoWave delivers the most robust 2.4 GHz PTP (Point to Point) solution on the market by coupling ultra-high output power, flexible channel width capability (5/10/20 MHz), and industry-leading proprietary software mechanisms. The LigoPTP 2 Series products offer carrier-class link connectivity, delivering true TCP throughput capability of 40 Mbps and packets-per-second performance of 35,000 PPS. The LigoPTP 2 series products offer an unlicensed PTP solution, ideal for dedicated access or backhaul applications (including VOIP) where other frequencies may be unavailable. The LigoPTP 2-N product features an external N-Connector for custom antenna application, delivering long-range, rock-solid link connectivity capability for the 2.4 GHz spectrum.</p><p>The LigoPTP 2-N showcases an array of advanced software mechanisms that provide optimal point-to-point connectivity for high-throughput, long distance links. LigoWave''s proprietary PTP mechanisms utilize techniques such as Dynamic Time Division Duplexing (TDD) to dynamically allocate bandwidth in the direction needed, thus increasing link efficiency and greatly decreasing the impact that distance has on throughput of the link. The LigoWave point-to-point products also feature selective repeat ARQ technology, an enhanced error-correction software mechanism that optimizes data traffic to provide very high throughput over high-bandwidth, long-range links even in the presence of interference. The LigoPTP 2-N is also compatible with WNMS, a centralized configuration, firmware, and statistics server offered by LigoWave for carrier class diagnostic and configuration management capabilities.</p><br />Product contains:<ul><li>High Output Power - adjustable</li><li>Adjustable Channel Width capability for throughput optimization</li><li>True TCP throughput up to 40 Mbps</li><li>35,000 packets-per-second (PPS) - ideal for VOIP backhaul applications</li><li>ARQ (Selective Repeat) for very high throughput</li><li>Dynamic TDD for bandwidth optimization</li><li>External N-Connector for custom antenna application</li><li>PoE built-in for single cable installation</li><li>Advanced security technologies</li><li>Comprehensive management features<ul><li>Web GUI</li><li>Command line management via SSH</li><li>WNMS server support for configuration</li><li>SNMP V1/2/3 with traps supporting MIBs: 802.1, 802.1x, MIBII</li><li>Syslog support</li></ul></li><li>Articulating Bracket Solution for multi-facet mounting</li></ul>', '<table id="whyligotable" align="left" border="0"><tbody><tr class="first"><td><img src="/uploads/features/Wjetb.thumbnail.png" alt="" height="73" width="100" /></td><td class="first" valign="top">70 Mbps of real TCP/IP throughput is&nbsp;ideal for large capacity applications.&nbsp;W-jet is Ligowave‘s proprietary <strong>wireless</strong> protocol that combines special techniques to achieve great performance and reliability even over long distances. &nbsp;The W-jet protocol is the result of years of development and gives Ligowave <strong>PTP products</strong> the ability to outperform other products on the market&nbsp; while simultaneously optimizing ROI for the customer.</td></tr><tr><td><object style="width: 90px; float: left; height: 90px;" data="/uploads/features/oras.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/oras.swf" /><param name="wmode" value="transparent" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/oras.swf" /></object></td><td style="text-align: left;" valign="top">IP67 standards conformant enclosure and <strong>carrier grade</strong> components tested under extreme weather conditions are used to build LigoWave equipment. Years of experience and customer feedback allows us to create a weatherproof design that is resistable to heavy rain, extremely hot and cold weather temperatures and other surprises that can make these days.</td></tr><tr><td scope="col" valign="top"><object data="/uploads/features/kelias.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/kelias.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/kelias.swf" /></object></td><td valign="top">LigoWave <strong>PTP equipment</strong> allows to establish connectivity even between very distant locations. This makes LigoPTP equipment suitable for rural connectivity where terrain is rough and power supply is very limited. &nbsp;Enormous potential available in rural areas should not be wasted and rapid return on investment using LigoWave solutions can be easily used by Internet service providers for quick expansion and use of the potential that is available in these areas.</td></tr><tr><td><object data="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" /></object></td><td>High spectral efficiency is typical for LigoPTP equipment.&nbsp; Combining digital signal processing, dual polarization <strong>antennas</strong> and proprietary W-Jet protocol these <strong>bridges</strong> have a high spectral efficiency of&nbsp;2.7 bit/Hz.</td></tr><tr><td><object data="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" /></object></td><td>OLED screen is installed in all the LigoPTP series radios. Using external OLED screen users can easily align the link, perform a link test with different packet sizes just after the deployment, find out various statistics about the link (<strong>wireless</strong>, ethernet, device status etc.), reset to defaults or reboot the device and even lock the equipment to avoid unvelcome impact.</td></tr><tr><td><object style="float: left;" data="/uploads/features/grafikas.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/grafikas.swf" /><param name="wmode" value="transparent" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/grafikas.swf" /></object></td><td>LigoWave‘s <strong>link calculator</strong> is a <strong>link planning tool</strong> available online at <a title="ptp linkplanner" href="http://www.ligowave.com/linkcalc" target="_blank">http://www.ligowave.com/linkcalc/</a>. The link calculator allows LigoPTP users to calculate link performance expectations taking into account geographical information, distance between the units, antenna height and gain, transmit power, and other factors in order to choose the most suitable product available from Ligowave‘s extensive product portfolio.</td></tr></tbody></table>', 0, '2012-08-31 06:21:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
