 is very limited. &nbsp;Enormous potential available in rural areas should not be wasted and rapid return on investment using LigoWave solutions can be easily used by Internet service providers for quick expansion and use of the potential that is available in these areas.</td></tr><tr><td><object data="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/bangos.swf" /></object></td><td>High spectral efficiency is typical for LigoPTP equipment.&nbsp; Combining digital signal processing, dual polarization <strong>antennas</strong> and proprietary W-Jet protocol these <strong>bridges</strong> have a high spectral efficiency of&nbsp;2.7 bit/Hz.</td></tr><tr><td><object data="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/RSSI.swf" /></object></td><td>OLED screen is installed in all the LigoPTP series radios. Using external OLED screen users can easily align the link, perform a link test with different packet sizes just after the deployment, find out various statistics about the link (<strong>wireless</strong>, ethernet, device status etc.), reset to defaults or reboot the device and even lock the equipment to avoid unvelcome impact.</td></tr><tr><td><object style="float: left;" data="/uploads/features/grafikas.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="90" width="90"><param name="data" value="/uploads/features/grafikas.swf" /><param name="wmode" value="transparent" /><param name="src" value="/uploads/features/grafikas.swf" /></object></td><td>LigoWave‘s <strong>link calculator</strong> is a <strong>link planning tool</strong> available online at <a title="ptp linkplanner" href="http://www.ligowave.com/linkcalc" target="_blank">http://www.ligowave.com/linkcalc/</a>. The link calculator allow